Religious freedom is guaranteed in Belize. According to the 2010 census40.1% of Belizeans are Roman Catholics, 31.8% are Protestants (8.4% Pentecostal; 5.4% Adventist; 4.7%AnglicanismAnglican; 3.7%Mennonite; 3.6%Baptist; 2.9%MethodismMethodist; 2.8% Nazarene), 1.7% areJehovah's Witnesses, 10.3% adhere to other religions (Maya religion,Garifuna religion,ObeahandMyalism, and minorities ofMormonismMormons,HinduismHindus,BuddhismBuddhists,IslamMuslims,Baha'i FaithBaha'is,Rastafariansand other) and 15.5% profess to be irreligious.
